{{Infobox person | name= Jackson Bond | birth_name = Jackson Bond |birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1996|4|3}} | birth_place = [[White Bear, Minnesota]] U.S. | occupation = [[Actor]] | years_active = 2006&ndash;present }}
'''Jackson Bond''' (born April 3, 1996) is an American actor. He starred in the 2007 film ''[[The Invasion (film)|The Invasion]]'', playing the part of Oliver and in the sitcom ''[[In Case of Emergency (TV series)|In Case of Emergency]]'' on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]].
==Life and career== Jackson Bond was born in [[White Bear Lake, Minnesota]]. Bond booked his first acting job in the feature film ''[[The Invasion (film)|The Invasion]]'' opposite [[Nicole Kidman]] at the age of nine. Less than a year later he landed the role of Dylan on ''[[In Case of Emergency (TV series)|In Case of Emergency]]''. He has also guest starred on ''[[CSI: Miami]]'' and appeared in films ''[[Killer Movie]]'' and ''Into Temptation''. He plays Jesse in the movie ''Return of Captain Kidd'', slated for [[2011 and beyond in film|2011]] release.
In his spare time Bond plays [[ice hockey]] and dances competitively.<ref>[http://www.kare11.com/news/news_article.aspx?storyid=108054 Minnesota boy hits it big in first movie role]</ref><ref>http://www.flixster.com/actor/jackson-bond</ref>
